## New Projects (Added 4 Apr 2026)

### Student Self-Help Skill Library
Searchable micro-lessons (2-5 min each) students can access on demand: "Using a caliper," "Writing a design brief," "How to give peer feedback," "Testing prototypes," "Reading technical drawings." Two sources: AI-generated from uploads (knowledge pipeline extracts methods as skill guides) or hand-curated by teacher.

**Key features:** floating "?" help button on student lesson pages with smart suggestions based on current activity context, search + filter pills + bookmarks, skill guides tagged by framework + activity type. Connects to MiniSkills concept (assignable micro-units) and existing toolkit tools.

**Build:** ~6-8 days. Spec: `docs/projects/self-help-library.md`. Depends on Dimensions3 Phase 2 (ingestion pipeline extracts skill content from uploads).

### Bug Button — In-App Reporting
Floating 🐛 button on platform with automatic context capture: URL, browser info, class context, console errors. Teacher enables per class via Class Hub settings. Admin Bug Reports tab with workflow (New → Investigating → Fixed → Closed). Reporter gets status update on next login. Issue deduplication. Sentry auto-linking for JS errors.

**Build:** ~2-3 days. Spec: `docs/projects/bug-button.md`. Already referenced in Dimensions3 spec §14.7. Low dependency — can be built anytime.

### Multi-Language Support / i18n
Teacher-selectable instruction language for international schools. 3 phases: Phase 1 (infrastructure — next-intl, JSON namespaced strings, per-class `instruction_language` + `additional_languages`), Phase 2 (student-facing UI translation — lesson pages, dashboard, toolkit, onboarding), Phase 3 (AI multilingual awareness — Design Assistant detects multilingual home, adapts scaffolding + sentence starters to student's language, TTS language matching).

**Build:** ~10-14 days across 3 phases. Spec: `docs/projects/i18n.md`. RTL + CJK support. Critical for international schools (Matt's primary market). Post-revenue initiative.

### Content Safety & Moderation
2-layer approach for student content: Tier 1 client-side keyword blocklist (instant, no API cost) + Tier 2 server-side AI moderation via Haiku classifier (context-aware, handles edge cases). 7 content streams needing moderation (text responses, AI assistant, toolkit tools, gallery reviews, reflections, bug reports, Quick Capture). Teacher Safety Alerts in Smart Insights panel. COPPA/KCSIE/eSafety/FERPA compliance.

**Build:** integrated into Dimensions3 phases (see spec §17). No separate build needed — moderation infrastructure grows as pipeline stages are built.

